<br>
/nitpick on.<br>
<br>
FYI, the door in HoT is meaningless.  The only thing doors affect in Everquest is whether or not a player character can run through them.  That's it. (well, they block archery and throwing weapons)  99.5% of the time, trains in HoT by the non-kos mobs on the other side of the door are the result of someone dragging a corpse that doesn't belong to them.  If anyone drags a corpse in ToV that doesn't belong to them, they will aggro any nearby mobs, independent of faction of the dragger and the faction of the corpse.  The only way to drag corpses their is by either running 5 steps forward, feigning, dragging, standing up, run 5 steps forward, rinse, repeat, or by dragging your own corpse.  For whatever reason, people choose to ignore this rule, and in the course of any given HoT raid you need to spam this warning over and over and over to not only the new invites but the people who have been to HoT 50+ times.  It's analogous to telling people to not bash PoH mobs up the wall and aggro'ing the second floor, or to not bash mobs onto firepots and/or trees, or to not attack the mezzed mobs.  You can ask every single individual member of the guild &quot;what did I tell you to not do 50 times?&quot; and each of them answer it right, but no matter what, every other time you go to hate you <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> will</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> bash a mob up the wall and get trained, you <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> will</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> get CT stuck in a tree, you <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> will</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> get mobs stuck on firepots, banners, or stairs, and some fuktard <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> will</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> consent his cleric buddy and his cleric buddy <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> will</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> drag the corpse out of ae and train your ass to freeport.  The real insidious thing about this is for whatever reason, said cleric and said dead person really honestly didn't see &quot;DON'T DRAG IF YOU'RE NOT A MONK&quot; spammed into raid chat 40 times and is wondering who the queefstain is that opened the door and got the guild trained.<br>
<br>
But yeah, the door being opened or closed will not affect the dynamics of aggro, spellcasting LOS, melee, or NPC pathing in any way.  Not sure where the HoT door myth came from but I really wish it would go away.<br>
<br>
/nitpick off.<br>
<br>
Trains can also be caused by the ae of the HoT kos to all mobs in camp hitting one of the hub CoV aligned mobs, which would cause trains that are seemingly without reason.  We've run into problems once or twice with kos to CoV people being CoH'd up and getting hub aggro a few times. (though this hasn't been a problem any time recently since we hosed our CoV faction and kill all the hub mobs to get to HoT) <p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
